ine and calcium concentrations. These improvements lead to\nincreased contrast-to-noise ratio (CNR) for both high and low contrast study\nobjects compared to EID-CT. PCCT can also generate super-high resolution (SHR)\nimages using much smaller detector pixel size than EID-CT and dramatically\nimprove image spatial resolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Dec 2022 01:51:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 11 Apr 2023 00:45:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-12"}
